if; overflow:hidden; text-align:left; margin:4px 8px 8px;\" data-lightboxfullscreendescriptionbottomcss=\"color:#fff; font-size:12px; font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; overflow:hidden; text-align:left; margin:4px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;\" data-lightboxsmallscreenheight=\"415\" data-lightboxbarheightonsmallheight=\"64\" data-lazyloadmode=\"none\" data-itemsperpage=\"12\" data-loadmorecaption=\"Load More\" data-loadmorecssstyle=\"wpp-loadmore-greybutton\" data-paginationcssstyle=\"wpp-pagination-greybutton\" data-paginationpos=\"bottom\" data-lightboxslideinterval=\"5000\" data-lightboxtimerposition=\"bottom\" data-lightboxtimercolor=\"#dc572e\" data-lightboxtimeropacity=\"1\" data-lightboxbordersize=\"8\" data-lightboxborderradius=\"0\" data-jsfolder=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/plugins/wonderplugin-gridgallery/engine/\" data-skinsfoldername=\"skins/default/\" style=\"display:none;position:relative;margin:0 auto;width:100%;max-width:608px;\" ><div class=\"wonderplugin-gridgallery-list\" style=\"display:block;position:relative;max-width:100%;margin:0 auto;\"><div class=\"wonderplugin-gridgallery-item\" data-row=\"1\" data-col=\"1\"><div class=\"wonderplugin-gridgallery-item-container\"><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"JavaScript:jQuery(\'#wonderplugingridgallery-23 .wonderplugin-gridgallery-item-img\').eq(0).click();return false;\" data-title=\"Animals\"><img class=\"wonderplugin-gridgallery-item-img\" alt=\"Animals\" src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/unsplash-dog3-600x400.jpeg\" /></a></div></div><div class=\"wonderplugin-gridgallery-item\" data-row=\"1\" data-col=\"1\"><div class=\"wonderplugin-gridgallery-item-container\"><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"JavaScript:jQuery(\'#wonderplugingridgallery-24 .wonderplugin-gridgallery-item-img\').eq(0).click();return false;\" data-title=\"Landscape\"><img class=\"wonderplugin-gridgallery-item-img\" alt=\"Landscape\" src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/lakeandballoon-600x407.jpeg\" /></a></div></div><div style=\"clear:both;\"></div></div><div style=\"clear:both;\"></div></div></div>\n<p>To create the above demo, we need to create three galleries: one grid gallery (the gallery displayed on the page) and two lightbox galleries.</p>\n<p>The grid gallery has two images, each image has its own lightbox gallery, so we need to create two lightbox galleries, one for each image.</p>\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong> - Create two lightbox galleries </p>\n<p>When creating the lightbox gallery, in the plugin, step 1 Images & Video tab, Add Image dialog, \"Lightbox and Weblink\" tab, make sure you check the option \"Click to open Lightbox popup\" -> \"Open current image in Lightbox\". This option is checked by default.</p>\n<p>In step 4 Options tab, select the option \"Lightbox gallery\" -> \"Only display first image in grid gallery and create a Lightbox gallery\".</p>\n<p>In this step, I created two lightbox galleries: ID 23 and ID 24.</p>\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong> - Create the grid gallery and link each image to its own lightbox gallery</p>\n<p>In <a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-gridgallery/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">WonderPlugin Portfolio Grid Gallery</a>, step 1, add an image, in the Add Image dialog, \"Lightbox and Weblink\" tab, uncheck the option \"Open current image in Lightbox\", enter <code>#</code> to the input box \"click to open web link\", enter the following code to the input box \"Set web link onclick code\":</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: jscript; title: ; notranslate\">\r\nJavaScript:jQuery(\'#wonderplugingridgallery-23 .wonderplugin-gridgallery-item-img\').eq(0).click();return false;\r\n</pre>\n<p>In the above code, 23 is the ID of the lightbox gallery we have created for this image. </p>\n<p><strong>Be sure to change the number to the ID of your own lightbox gallery of this image.</strong></p>\n<p><a class=\"wplightbox\" href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/lightbox-gallery.png\"><img src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/lightbox-gallery.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"814\" height=\"550\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-5773\" srcset=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/lightbox-gallery.png 814w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/lightbox-gallery-240x162.png 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/lightbox-gallery-600x405.png 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/lightbox-gallery-768x519.png 768w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/lightbox-gallery-75x51.png 75w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/lightbox-gallery-444x300.png 444w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 814px) 100vw, 814px\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>Please note, currently the following gallery skins do not work with this tutorial: \"Hover\", \"3D Flip\", \"3D Flip with Title\" and \"Circular 3D Flip\". Please do not select these skins when you create the final gallery.</strong></p>\n<p>In this step, I created the grid gallery: ID 35. </p>\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong> - Add shortcodes of the lightbox galleries and the grid gallery to the post or page</p>\n<p>In your WordPress post or page editor, <strong>switch to Text mode</strong>, then add the following code:</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\">\r\n&lt;div style=&quot;display:none;&quot;&gt;\r\n[wonderplugin_gridgallery id=23]\r\n[wonderplugin_gridgallery id=24]\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n \r\n[wonderplugin_gridgallery id=35]\r\n</pre>\n<p>ID 23 and ID 24 are lightbox galleries created in step 1. ID 35 is the grid gallery created in step 2.</p>\n<p>To hide the lightbox galleries by default so they can only be opened by the grid gallery, the shortcodes are wrapped inside a div that has the CSS style display:none.</p>\n<p>The grid gallery contains two images. The first image will open the lightbox gallery ID 23, the second image will open the lightbox gallery ID 24.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"I have renewed by license, but I still can not update my plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:112:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-tutorials/i-have-renewed-by-license-but-i-still-can-not-update-my-plugin/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 16 Mar 2018 04:11:07 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/?p=5725\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:434:\"Product: All WonderPlugin Products Question: I renewed my license just now, but in my WordPress backend, I still get the message \"Your free upgrade period has expired. To get automatic update, please renew your license\" and hence can not update &#8230; <a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-tutorials/i-have-renewed-by-license-but-i-still-can-not-update-my-plugin/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"WonderPlugin Support\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3336:\"<p><strong>Product</strong>:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">All WonderPlugin Products</a></p>\n<p><strong>Question</strong>:</p>\n<p>I renewed my license just now, but in my WordPress backend, I still get the message \"Your free upgrade period has expired. To get automatic update, please renew your license\" and hence can not update the plugin.<br />\n<span id=\"more-5725\"></span></p>\n<p><a class=\"wplightbox\" href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-plugin-update-error.png\"><img src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-plugin-update-error-600x126.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"126\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-5740\" srcset=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-plugin-update-error-600x126.png 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-plugin-update-error-240x50.png 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-plugin-update-error-75x16.png 75w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-plugin-update-error-500x105.png 500w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-plugin-update-error.png 751w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>Answer</strong>:</p>\n<p>Firstly, please make sure you have used the email address of your existing account to renew or upgrade your license, otherwise a new account will be created. If this has happened to you, please contact our support team at <a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/contact/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.wonderplugin.com/contact/</a>, we will merge your renew to your existing account.</p>\n<p>Once your have renewed or upgraded, a new login password will be emailed to you. Please use the new password to log into the members area. Your license will also have been automatically extended. </p>\n<p>WordPress caches all the plugin information, so in your WordPress backend, you may still get the message \"Automatic update is unavailable for this plugin. Your free upgrade period has expired. To get automatic update, please renew your license.\".</p>\n<p>To clear the cache and speed up the process, in your WordPress backend, left menu, click the menu item Dashboard -> Updates, then click the button \"Check Again\". You may need to click the buttons several times.</p>\n<p><a class=\"wplightbox\" href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-checkagain.png\"><img src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-checkagain-600x275.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"275\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-5736\" srcset=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-checkagain-600x275.png 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-checkagain-240x110.png 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-checkagain-75x34.png 75w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-checkagain-500x229.png 500w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-checkagain.png 674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>If it\'s still not working, please log out of your WordPress, wait for several hours and login again.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"How to enable WordPress mobile detect on Siteorigin Page Builder\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:118:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-mobile-detect/how-to-enable-wordpress-mobile-detect-on-siteorigin-page-builder/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 15 Mar 2018 21:44:01 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"WordPress Mobile Detect\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/?p=5718\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:409:\"Product: WordPress Mobile Detect Question: I am looking for a solution to be able to serve different content to mobile and tablet - desktop. Your plugin seems to be one of the few around, but I build my sites with &#8230; <a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-mobile-detect/how-to-enable-wordpress-mobile-detect-on-siteorigin-page-builder/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"WonderPlugin Support\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1683:\"<p><strong>Product</strong>:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-conditional-display-for-mobile/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress Mobile Detect</a></p>\n<p><strong>Question</strong>:</p>\n<p>I am looking for a solution to be able to serve different content to mobile and tablet - desktop. Your plugin seems to be one of the few around, but I build my sites with Siteorigin Page Builder, so I guess the shortcode wrapping will not work.</p>\n<p>Is there any other way of getting this functionality that you can recommend, as far as integrating with a page builder?</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-5718\"></span></p>\n<p><strong>Answer</strong>:</p>\n<p>Siteorigin Page Builder supports shortcode.</p>\n<p>In Siteorigin page editor, click the button \"Add Widget\", find the widget \"Text\", then you can edit the Text widget content and enter the shortcode.</p>\n<p><a class=\"wplightbox\" href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/siteorigin-shortcode.png\"><img src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/siteorigin-shortcode-600x296.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"296\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-5719\" srcset=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/siteorigin-shortcode-600x296.png 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/siteorigin-shortcode-240x118.png 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/siteorigin-shortcode-75x37.png 75w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/siteorigin-shortcode-500x247.png 500w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/siteorigin-shortcode.png 693w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a> </p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38:\"Delay the start of audio auto playback\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-audio-player/delay-the-start-of-audio-auto-playback/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sun, 11 Mar 2018 07:33:51 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"WordPress Audio Player\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"WordPress Audio Player Plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/?p=5709\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:398:\"Product: WonderPlugin Audio Player Question: I am using the audio play plugin. I have setup the player to auto play on page load. Is there anyway to delay the start of the playback, without actually changing the audio content? Be &#8230; <a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-audio-player/delay-the-start-of-audio-auto-playback/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"WonderPlugin Support\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1006:\"<p><strong>Product</strong>:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-audio-player/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">WonderPlugin Audio Player</a></p>\n<p><strong>Question</strong>:</p>\n<p>I am using the audio play plugin. I have setup the player to auto play on page load. Is there anyway to delay the start of the playback, without actually changing the audio content? Be nice to have a setting that says \"delay play\" for X seconds.<br />\n<span id=\"more-5709\"></span></p>\n<p><strong>Answer</strong>:</p>\n<p>1. In the plugin, step 3 Options tab, Skin Options, check the option \"Play mode\" -> \"Auto play (not working on mobile and tablets)\".</p>\n<p>2. In the plugin, step 3 Options tab, Advanced Options, add the following code to the <code>Advanced Options</code> input box. This will delay the play for 10 seconds (10000 milliseconds). Please note, audio auto play won\'t work on Android and iOS devices. </p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\">\r\ndata-autoplaytimeout=10000\r\n</pre>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"How to create a WordPress Radionomy player\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:104:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-audio-player-tutorial/how-to-create-a-wordpress-radionomy-player/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 03 Mar 2018 01:31:52 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"WordPress Audio Player\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"WordPress Audio Player Plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"WordPress Audio Player Tutorial\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/?p=5696\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:447:\"Product: WonderPlugin Audio Player Tutorial: This tutorial will guide you how to create a WordPress Radionomy player with the plugin WonderPlugin Audio Player. Step 1: In WonderPlugin Audio Player, step 1, click the button \"Add Audio\", enter the Radionomy streaming &#8230; <a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-audio-player-tutorial/how-to-create-a-wordpress-radionomy-player/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"WonderPlugin Support\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1802:\"<p><strong>Product</strong>:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-audio-player/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">WonderPlugin Audio Player</a></p>\n<p><strong>Tutorial</strong>:</p>\n<p>This tutorial will guide you how to create a WordPress Radionomy player with the plugin WonderPlugin Audio Player.<br />\n<span id=\"more-5696\"></span></p>\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong>:</p>\n<p>In WonderPlugin Audio Player, step 1, click the button \"Add Audio\", enter the Radionomy streaming URL to the \"Mp3 URL\" input box, check the option \"This is a live streaming\".</p>\n<p>If you would like to display the played track list, enter the radioUID of the Radionomy station.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-radionomy-player.png\" class=\"wplightbox\"><img src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-radionomy-player-600x446.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"446\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-5699\" srcset=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-radionomy-player-600x446.png 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-radionomy-player-240x178.png 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-radionomy-player-75x56.png 75w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-radionomy-player-404x300.png 404w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-radionomy-player.png 731w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong>:</p>\n<p>In the plugin, step 2, Skins tab, choose a skin from the skin list. If you would like to display the played track list, choose the skin \"White Box Live\" or \"Grey Box Live\". These two skins are created specifically for live streaming.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:34:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";O:42:\"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary\":1:{s:7:\"\0*\0data\";a:9:{s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Sat, 14 Apr 2018 08:03:06 GMT\";s:6:\"server\";s:22:\"Apache/2.2.15 (CentOS)\";s:12:\"x-powered-by\";s:9:\"PHP/5.3.3\";s:13:\"last-modified\";s:29:\"Fri, 13 Apr 2018 11:42:53 GMT\";s:4:\"link\";s:65:\"<https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-json/>; rel=\"https://api.w.org/\"\";s:4:\"vary\";s:26:\"Accept-Encoding,User-Agent\";s:16:\"content-encoding\";s:4:\"gzip\";s:14:\"content-length\";s:5:\"13290\";s:12:\"content-type\";s:34:\"application/rss+xml; charset=UTF-8\";}}s:5:\"build\";s:14:\"20130910223210\";}', 'no');
